        <p>Judgment translation requires precision in legal terminology that general translators rarely possess. The <span class="hero-highlight">operative part</span> (the actual court order), the legal reasoning, and any conditions or timelines must be rendered exactly. Ambiguity in translation could affect enforcement entirely or create grounds for challenge. A poorly translated verdict can derail enforcement proceedings that should have been straightforward.</p>

